Description:
Minimal failing example:
typedef struct packed {
    union packed {
        logic[2:0] a;
        logic[2:0] b;
    } u;
} s1;

module top(input s1 inp, output logic out);
    assign out = | inp.u.a;
endmodule
Fails with the following
$ iverilog test.sv -o build/a.out -g2012
test.sv:10: assert: elab_expr.cc:6330: failed assertion expr_type_ != IVL_VT_NO_TYPE
Aborted (core dumped)

However, assign out = | (inp.u.a | 0) succeeds. As does a union by itself:
typedef union packed {
    logic[2:0] a;
    logic[2:0] b;
} s1;

module top(input s1 inp, output logic out);
    assign out = | inp.a;
endmodule
